Hong Kong Stocks Loses 1.2 Percent 
Hong Kong stocks lost 122.06 points, or 1.19 percent, to close at
10,170.14 after a day of low trading Monday.
The turnover was 1,222 million HK dollars (about 157 million U.S.
dollars), 292 million HK dollars (about 37 million U.S. dollars) less
than that of the previous trading day.
After a three-day break since Christmas, the market opened slightly
lower Monday morning with the Hang Seng Index going down 28.58 points,
or 0.28 percent, to 10,263.62.
The HSI was then 61.64 points, or 0.6 percent, lower to finish the
morning session at 10,230.56.
The share prices gained 133.45 points, or 1.31 percent, to close at
10,292.2 on Thursday.
